{"questionId":"305aaf32-2803-4909-83d0-d08ba71a35a7_17","correctAnswer":"25515","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Substitute the given values","content":"Use $x=1.25$, $y=1968.75$ in $y=900ax^2$: $$1968.75 = 900a(1.25)^2 = 1406.25a \\Rightarrow a=1.4.$$"},{"title":"Solve for the unknown","content":"Now use $x=4.5$: $$y = 900(1.4)(4.5)^2 = 1260 \\cdot 20.25 = 25515.$$ The answer is <strong>25515</strong>."}]}